{"id": "QmZpJ1xrL77Vk2KRMwtRnXWzSLEmnicLKDcW7fu9wVK6aD", "title": "Merging of the IdleTokenGovernace adaptive fix for Aave V2 with Pilot League IIP", "body": "### Summary\n\nAccording to the [Aave\u2019s roadmap](https://governance.aave.com/t/aave-protocol-v1-v2-migration-tool-and-transition-plan/2053), the migration from V1 to V2 should happen in about one month. Even if this deadline might be extended, Idle protocol should schedule this update on time.\n\nAfter drafting the new required [wrapper](https://github.com/Idle-Labs/idle-contracts/blob/aave-v2/contracts/wrappers/IdleAaveV2.sol) we noticed that the main IdleTokenGovernance implementation (shared among all idleTokens) requires a small change in the contract, in order to correctly support the addition of new wrappers.\n\nPilot\u2019s elections are now closed and the on-chain proposal will come in a few days, so we can speed up its execution by merging this change with the main proposal.\n\nNo concerns have been expressed in the [Forum post](https://gov.idle.finance/t/idletokengovernace-adaptive-fix-for-aave-v2/244).\n\n\n### Details\n\n[A fix has been proposed here](https://github.com/Idle-Labs/idle-contracts/pull/1/files)\n\nVote \u201c**FOR**\u201d, if you agree to merge the adaptive fix with the upcoming League\u2019s IIP.\n\nVote \u201c**AGAINST**\u201d, if you do not want to see the implementation of the adaptive fix.\n\nVote \u201c**Discuss more**\u201d, if you have concerns about the implementation approach.\n\nSnapshot is an off-chain solution to cast a vote by signature, no gas spent.\n", "choices": ["FOR", "AGAINST", "Discuss more"], "start": 1613057400, "end": 1613316600, "snapshot": "11836150", "state": "closed", "author": "0x2fa92128ecE3901395448bf62Dd5Ff6a35871540", "space": {"id": "idlefinance.eth", "name": "Idle"}, "votes": 51, "votes_data": [{"id": "Qmdg27nJ6DDgbPmDAxLLVLrgSDLCFyZWfZea5JSY8QnH8P", "voter": "0x344e6ED6525a0F36AB03819a7b7b99F33b3FD1ce", "created": 1613295469, "choice": 1, "spa